t-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Yes. Enter YTD amounts for each earnings and deduction row. YTD totals appear on the PDF when present. When you duplicate a stub from history for a new pay period, YTD values carry over.\"}]]}],\"$L4a\",\"$L4b\",\"$L4c\"]}]]}]\n3b:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Mixing gross and net in the same column\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"A pay stub lists gross pay, then deductions, then net pay — in that order. Putting net in the earnings column makes the math look wrong to anyone (lender, landlord, accountant) reviewing the stub.\"}]]}]\n3c:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Forgetting employer contributions\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$36:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Forgetting employer contributions\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Employer-side contributions (employer 401(k) match, FICA) don't reduce employee net pay but should appear on the stub for completeness. Adding them avoids questions later.\"}]]}]]}]\n3d:[\"$\",\"li\",\"Using a generic deduction label\",{\"className\":\"flex gap-3 rounded-lg border border-border bg-card p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{\"ref\":\"$undefined\",\"iconNode\":\"$36:1:props:children:1:props:children:0:props:children:0:props:iconNode\",\"className\":\"lucide-triangle-alert mt-0.5 size-5 shrink-0 text-pink-500\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm font-semibold\",\"children\":\"Using a generic deduction label\"}],